node.text: Pizza party with elephants! This was an especially memorable day, not only for the food 🤤 but also for the unexpected guests! Today's lesson for the kids' Summer Semester on Safari was a cooking class; Dorothy likes to calls them her "Cooking Corner". The chefs at @africanbushcamps in Zimbabwe were so great with the kids and halfway through the cooking class we were surrounded by a parade of elephants (which were also pretty great with the kids too😉)!

node.text: GIRLS TURN!! 😩😱😅 Once again, another example of a parent TRYING to put on a brave face for their child!! Can you hear what Dorothy says at the very end?? 😳

node.text:
There are some ups AND downs to traveling right now : 1 of the downs is how tricky logistics have become due to Covid testing most every time we switch a country or destination. BUT the ups have far outweighed the downs! Perhaps the biggest up so far has been seeing just how much it means to the countries and lodges and tour companies to be open again. Most of our stops thus far we have been their 1st guests since reopening. They are thrilled and just so grateful to be open again. We love to travel because the positive effect it has on our kids and family..BUT so grateful when we can return the favor and be a source of some good to the places we visit as well.. 😌❤️🌎💚🥰
/// @matetsivictoriafalls

node.text: Do you see it in the background?? 🐘 I’m so grateful to be here, on safari, in the bush, seeing these magnificent animals in their wild habitat. We just arrived at the beautiful @matetsivictoriafalls in Zimbabwe 🇿🇼. You can see in our Instagram stories today that the moment our safari jeep left the camp to explore for animals Garrett says, “You’re in your happy place right now..” and right then I begin to cry.. 😭🥰😭
